-- Norway's oil fund buys London properties for $576 mln
-- 
-- Mon Aug 11, 2014 01:10AM EDT
-- None



OSLO, Aug 11 (Reuters) - Norway's $870 billion oil fund purchased a 57.8 percent stake in the 730,000-square-foot Pollen Estate in London's West End for 343 million pounds ($575.59 million), the fund said in a statement.

The estate, which consists of 43 assets with a mix of retail and office space, was bought from the Church Commissioners for England and the property will be managed by Pollen Estate trustee company.